First Lady Michelle Obama and Oprah Winfrey will be having a conversation at The United State of Women Summit on June 14th in Washington, DC. The conversation will focus on inspiring the next generation of women and highlighting the progress women have made. The summit will cover various topics including gender equality, economic empowerment, health and wellness, education, violence, entrepreneurship, leadership, and civic participation. The goal of the summit is to encourage women to take action and make a difference in their collective future.